  "prompt": "I am 17. Should I start taking multivitamins as a supplement to my diet?",
  "response": "Whether you should take multivitamins depends on several factors:\n\nPros of taking multivitamins:\n1. Can help fill nutritional gaps in your diet\n2. May support overall health and development\n3. Beneficial if you have dietary restrictions or limited food variety\n\nCons/Considerations:\n1. A balanced diet is usually the best source of nutrients\n2. Some vitamins can be harmful in excess\n3. Not all multivitamins are created equal\n\nWhen multivitamins might be recommended:\n- Vegetarian/vegan diet\n- Restricted calorie intake\n- Specific health conditions\n- Limited access to varied, nutritious foods\n\nBest approach:\n1. Consult your healthcare provider\n2. Get a blood test to check for specific nutritional deficiencies\n3. Focus on eating a balanced, varied diet first\n4. Consider a multivitamin if recommended by a professional\n\nSpecific nutrients to pay attention to at your age:\n- Calcium\n- Iron\n- Vitamin D\n- B vitamins\n\nRemember: Individual nutritional needs vary, so personalized medical advice is always best.",
